  "lastReviewFeedback": "coderabbitai: **Actionable comments posted: 3**\n\n<details>\n<summary>🤖 Prompt for all review comments with AI agents</summary>\n\n```\nVerify each finding against the current code and only fix it if needed.\n\nInline comments:\nIn `@packages/tailwind-preset/package.json`:\n- Around line 6-15: The package.json currently points \"main\", \"types\", and the\n\"exports\" entries at ./src/index.ts and includes \"files\": [\"src\"], which\npublishes TypeScript sources instead of compiled artifacts; update those entries\nto point to the compiled outputs in ./dist (e.g., set \"main\" and \"exports\".\".\"\nto ./dist/index.js and \"types\" to ./dist/index.d.ts) and change \"files\" to\ninclude \"dist\". Also add a \"build\" script in \"scripts\" (e.g., \"build\": \"tsc -p\ntsconfig.json\") so the dist and .d.ts files are generated before publish.\n- Around line 19-24: The peerDependencies range for \"tailwindcss\" is too low for\nthe preset's darkMode API; update the peerDependencies \"tailwindcss\" entry to\nrequire at least the version that introduced selector darkMode (e.g. change to\n\"^3.4.1\") so the preset's darkMode: ['selector', '[data-theme=\"dark\"]'] in\npackages/tailwind-preset/src/index.ts is supported; also consider aligning the\ndevDependencies tailwindcss version to >=3.4.1 to match testing/build tooling.\n\nIn `@packages/tailwind-preset/src/index.ts`:\n- Around line 307-313: The screens mapping currently uses CSS custom properties\n(the screens constant) which produce invalid `@media` rules; replace the ref(...)\nvalues with static breakpoint strings (e.g., '576px', '768px', '992px',\n'1200px', '1400px' or Tailwind's default\n'640px','768px','1024px','1280px','1536px') so theme.screens is built from\nconcrete pixel values; update the screens Record in\npackages/tailwind-preset/src/index.ts (the screens constant) to use those static\nstrings and remove ref(...) there so Tailwind outputs valid `@media` (min-width:\n...) rules.\n```\n\n</details>\n\n---\n\n<details>\n<summary>ℹ️ Review info</summary>\n\n<details>\n<summary>⚙️ Run configu",
